## Samples that have failed the contamination check

data %>%

        5) %>%

Question 3

## selecting only columns with numeric columns and renaming them
data_num <- data %>%
    select(1, where(is.numeric)) %>%
    rename_with(stringr::str_replace, pattern = "quast.", replacement = "", matches("quast.")) %>%
    rename_with(stringr::str_replace, pattern = ".metric_value", replacement = "",
        matches(".metric_value")) %>%
    rename(contamination_percent = confindr.percentage_contamination)

Question 4

## obtaining names of column of data
colnames(data_num)
[1] "sample_name"               "contamination_percent"    
[3] "# contigs (>= 1000 bp)"    "N50"                      
[5] "Total length (>= 1000 bp)"
## range of total length
range(data_num$`Total length (>= 1000 bp)`)
[1]  6039230 13523259
## Boxplot of Total length (>= 1000bp)
ggplot(data_num) + geom_boxplot(aes(`Total length (>= 1000 bp)`)) + scale_x_continuous(minor_breaks = seq(6e+06,
    1.4e+07, by = 5e+05), labels = label_number(suffix = "", scale = 1e-06)) + labs(title = "Box blot showing total length (>= 1000 bp)",
    x = "Total length (in millions)")

Question 5

## tidying the data
data_pivot <- data_num %>%
    pivot_longer(!sample_name, names_to = "metric", values_to = "value")

Question 6

## Violin plot of numeric variables with jittered data points
ggplot(data_pivot, aes(metric, value)) + geom_violin() + geom_jitter(position = position_jitter(seed = 1,
    width = 0.1)) + scale_y_continuous(trans = "log2") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60,
    hjust = 1, size = 10), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10), axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 15)) + ggtitle("Violin plot showing distribution of numerical variables in a QC spreadsheet")
